    "sub_topic": "Traveling salesman problem",
    "message_1": "A traveling salesman needs to visit 5 cities in one day. The distance between the cities are as follows: \n\nCity 1 to City 2: 10 km\nCity 1 to City 3: 15 km\nCity 1 to City 4: 20 km\nCity 1 to City 5: 25 km\nCity 2 to City 3: 12 km\nCity 2 to City 4: 18 km\nCity 2 to City 5: 24 km\nCity 3 to City 4: 8 km\nCity 3 to City 5: 16 km\nCity 4 to City 5: 10 km\n\nWhat is the shortest possible distance (in km) that the salesman can travel to visit all 5 cities starting and ending in City 1?",
    "message_2": "To find the shortest possible distance, we need to consider all possible routes and calculate their total distances. Since the salesman starts and ends in City 1, we only need to consider the permutations of the other 4 cities. There are 4! (4 factorial) permutations, which is 4 × 3 × 2 × 1 = 24 possible routes.\n\nHere are the 24 possible routes and their total distances:\n\n1. 1-2-3-4-5-1: 10+12+8+10+25 = 65 km\n2. 1-2-3-5-4-1: 10+12+16+18+20 = 76 km\n3. 1-2-4-3-5-1: 10+18+8+16+25 = 77 km\n4. 1-2-4-5-3-1: 10+18+10+16+15 = 69 km\n5. 1-2-5-3-4-1: 10+24+16+8+20 = 78 km\n6. 1-2-5-4-3-1: 10+24+10+8+15 = 67 km\n7. 1-3-2-4-5-1: 15+12+18+10+25 = 80 km\n8. 1-3-2-5-4-1: 15+12+24+18+20 = 89 km\n9. 1-3-4-2-5-1: 15+8+18+24+25 = 90 km\n10. 1-3-4-5-2-1: 15+8+10+24+10 = 67 km\n11. 1-3-5-2-4-1: 15+16+24+18+20 = 93 km\n12. 1-3-5-4-2-1: 15+16+10+18+10 = 69 km\n13. 1-4-2-3-5-1: 20+18+12+16+25 = 91 km\n14. 1-4-2-5-3-1: 20+18+24+16+15 = 93 km\n15. 1-4-3-2-5-1: 20+8+12+24+25 = 89 km\n16. 1-4-3-5-2-1: 20+8+16+24+10 = 78 km\n17. 1-4-5-2-3-1: 20+10+24+12+15 = 81 km\n18. 1-4-5-3-2-1: 20+10+16+12+10 = 68 km\n19. 1-5-2-3-4-1: 25+24+12+8+20 = 89 km\n20. 1-5-2-4-3-1: 25+24+18+8+15 = 90 km\n21. 1-5-3-2-4-1: 25+16+12+18+20 = 91 km\n22. 1-5-3-4-2-1: 25+16+8+18+10 = 77 km\n23. 1-5-4-2-3-1: 25+10+18+12+15 = 80 km\n24. 1-5-4-3-2-1: 25+10+8+12+10 = 65 km\n\nThe shortest possible distance is 65 km, which can be achieved by following either route 1 (1-2-3-4-5-1) or route 24 (1-5-4-3-2-1)."
